: This species is the only member of 
<taxonomicName id="4C033DD8FF93996F1F80FA266628F9AA" authorityName="Leavengood, Pinkerton and Rifkind" authorityYear="2022" box="[738,880,1518,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarsobaenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF93996F1F80FA266628F9AA" box="[738,880,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">Tarsobaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacking a black elytral fascia. Except for the extreme epipleural margin, the elytra are concolorous orange.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31915D0FF93996F1DA5F9FD6055F9D7" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBC465BFF93996F1DA5F9FD6055F9D7" blockId="6.[151,1437,1517,1832]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF93996F1DA5F9FD6460F9ED" bold="true" box="[199,312,1589,1615]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">Variation</emphasis>
: Black markings on the lateral margins of the pronotum and elytra are absent in the more brightly colored 
<typeStatus id="54B8F8F9FF93996F1D90F992640AF9D6" box="[242,338,1626,1652]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">paratype</typeStatus>
(approx.. 
<quantity id="4CFBEBBEFF93996F1CA4F9916775F9D6" box="[454,557,1625,1652]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.94" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="5.94">5.94 mm</quantity>
; specimen with head projecting and abdomen perhaps distended).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31915D0FF93996F1DA5F9B567FEF942" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BBC465BFF93996F1DA5F9B567FEF942" blockId="6.[151,1437,1517,1832]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF93996F1DA5F9B56479F935" bold="true" box="[199,289,1661,1687]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">Biology</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF923BAAFF93996F1C52F9B66759F93A" author="Letourneau, D. K." box="[304,513,1662,1688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" pagination="215 - 217" refId="ref7504" refString="Letourneau, D. K. (1990) Code of ant-plant mutualism broken by parasite. Science, 248, 215 - 217. https: // doi. org / 10.1126 / science. 248.4952.215" type="journal article" year="1990">Letourneau (1990)</bibRefCitation>
observed 
<taxonomicName id="4C033DD8FF93996F1F11F9B66791F935" authorityName="Leavengood &amp; Pinkerton &amp; Rifkind" authorityYear="2022" box="[627,713,1662,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarsobaenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piper">
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF93996F1F11F9B66791F935" box="[627,713,1662,1687]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">T. piper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the petiole chambers of 
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF93996F1E9AF9B6619CF93A" box="[1016,1220,1662,1688]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">Piper cenocladum</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C033DD8FF93996F19B0F9B66017F93B" box="[1234,1359,1662,1689]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Piperaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Piperaceae</taxonomicName>
) in the presence of plant-produced food bodies. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF923BAAFF93996F1F07F96A666FF91E" author="Letourneau, D. K." box="[613,823,1698,1724]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" pagination="4 - 8" refId="ref7541" refString="Letourneau, D. K. (1993) Ants that pay the Piper. Natural History, 102 (10), 4 - 8." type="journal article" year="1993">Letourneau (1993)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that both 
<taxonomicName id="4C033DD8FF93996F1943F96A6121F919" authorityName="Leavengood &amp; Pinkerton &amp; Rifkind" authorityYear="2022" box="[1057,1145,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarsobaenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piper">
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF93996F1943F96A6121F919" box="[1057,1145,1698,1723]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">T. piper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C033DD8FF93996F19D3F96A604DF91E" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1839" box="[1201,1301,1698,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF93996F19D3F96A604DF91E" box="[1201,1301,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">Pheidole</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ants induce food body production by chemical stimulation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31915D0FF93996F1DA5F92166CFF8A6" box="[199,919,1769,1796]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BBC465BFF93996F1DA5F92166CFF8A6" blockId="6.[151,1437,1517,1832]" box="[199,919,1769,1796]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF93996F1DA5F9216401F8A1" bold="true" box="[199,345,1769,1795]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">Distribution</emphasis>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C788B9FF93996F1C0AF9226491F8A6" box="[360,457,1770,1796]" country="Costa Rica" name="San Jose" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">San Jose</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49C788B9FF93996F1F62F9226723F8A6" box="[512,635,1770,1796]" country="Costa Rica" name="Puntarenas" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">Puntarenas</collectingRegion>
Provinces of 
<collectingCountry id="F31406CBFF93996F1E77F92266CBF8A6" box="[789,915,1770,1796]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31915D0FF93996F1DA5F8C66054F88A" box="[199,1292,1806,1832]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BBC465BFF93996F1DA5F8C66054F88A" blockId="6.[151,1437,1517,1832]" box="[199,1292,1806,1832]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF93996F1DA5F8C66410F88A" bold="true" box="[199,328,1806,1832]" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">Etymology</emphasis>
: This species is named after the genus (
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF93996F1E6AF8C6661EF885" box="[776,838,1806,1831]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="173">Piper</emphasis>
) of the plant with which it is associated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
